articles.title: World's Largest Known Asteroid Impact Structure Beneath Earth in Southeast Australia - ummid.com
articles.description: The world’s largest asteroid impact structure is buried deep under the Earth in southern New South Wales, Australia, researchers said based on many years of experience in asteroid impact.
articles.content: [When an asteroid strikes, it creates a crater with an uplifted core. This is similar to how a drop of water splashes upward from a transient crater when you drop a pebble in a pool (Image credit: NA… [+3326 chars]
